OL,5,EDEAR 'ZINE                S/--&Q+'S.+.+
OL,7,BHey, isn't summer great? Great         
OL,8,Bconcerts, great cricket, great weather.
OL,9,BAnd to to top it all, I've just got    
OL,10,Bmyself a great new girlfriend.         
OL,11,B                                      B
OL,12,BOn the other hand, in two weeks time   
OL,13,BI'll be broke, we'll have lost the     
OL,14,Bcricket, everyone will have gone on    
OL,15,Bholiday to Barbados and I'll be two    
OL,16,Bweeks closer to a pile of A level work 
OL,17,Bfor a couple of years. Still, thank God
OL,18,Bfor Quincy and Ready, Steady, Cook on  
OL,19,Bweekdays.EPeter Buck's Funky Plectrum  
